                text = "*(A spare, sharp woman amid scrolls in scripts no living mouth can speak, who looks up at you and *flinches* — then leans in, hungry.)* Stand still. *(she circles you, reading the air.)* You carry a word. Half-formed. In a script I — *(she stops, and her sharpness cracks into wonder.)* — in a script I have only ever seen *carved.* Never *spoken.* The tongue of the very first sorting, the language the Wall was *written* in, dead ten thousand years and read by no one because no one *living* was ever named in it. *(she meets your eyes.)* Until you. You've a name in the dead tongue, Returned. Half-set. And I am the only soul in the Realms who can teach you to read it. The question is whether either of us is brave enough.",
