                text = "*(She is quiet a long moment.)* What it costs. *(she touches a scroll.)* A dead language is a *graveyard*, Returned. To read it fluently you must let the dead *speak in your own mind* — you must give them your living tongue to borrow, so their words can sound again. *(quietly.)* I flinched at you because I have spent sixty years lending my mind to the long dead, and you are a thing that came *back*, and for one moment I feared you'd come to *collect* the loan — to take back all the borrowed voices I've kept alive in here. *(a thin smile.)* You haven't. You've come to *add* one. So the cost is this: read your name, and you let ten thousand years of the dead a little further into your living head. *(she meets your eyes.)* I've borne it sixty years and it's made me strange and solitary and, I think, *better.* But I'd not lie to you about the weight. The dead are heavy company. They're also the only company that never leaves.",
